<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_CAS_FaceBody_FaceSculpting" s="315390">
  <T n="name">0xF35DB253<!--String: "Face Sculpting"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_FaceSculpting_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d0ab0e517194c2b7</T>
      <T n="text">0x7C08B9AE<!--String: "When <b><font color='#199C2C'>sculpting</font></b> a Sim’s face, you have two main tools at your disposal: <b><font color='#199C2C'>Presets</font></b>, and <b><font color='#199C2C'>clicking and dragging</font></b>! \n\nBy combining various Presets for the different parts of your Sim’s face, you can quickly create a unique look. Then you can customize it in detail by clicking and dragging to make their face match your imagination!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_FaceSculpting_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d0ab0e517194c2b4</T>
      <T n="text">0x121999A5<!--String: "The most basic Preset is the full <b><font color='#199C2C'>Face Preset</font></b>. Select your Sim's face and choose the Face option in the menu to access the Faces catalog. These are unique facial archetypes that you can select to make your Sims look appropriate for different ethnicities. \n\nYou cannot achieve the look of one shape by manipulating another, so choose carefully!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_FaceSculpting_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d0ab0e517194c2b5</T>
      <T n="text">0x64D834D4<!--String: "Then there are Presets for <b><font color='#199C2C'>each part</font></b> of the Sim’s face: Eyes, Nose, Mouth, Head Shape, Cheek, Jaw, Chin, and Ears. Simply select that part of your Sim’s face, and the selection of Presets will appear.\n\nSome Presets have <b><font color='#199C2C'>unique characteristics</font></b> that can’t be created by clicking and dragging, such as chin dimples."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_FaceSculpting_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d0ab0e517194c2b2</T>
      <T n="text">0xBFDB46C4<!--String: "You can adjust the <b><font color='#199C2C'>scale</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>position</font></b>, and (in certain cases) even <b><font color='#199C2C'>rotation</font></b> of each part of your Sim’s face! Click and drag on your Sim’s face to experiment.\n\nDepending on where you placed the cursor, you will manipulate a face part in different ways. For example, selecting the inner corner of the eyes allows you to rotate it, while selecting the outer corner resizes the eyes instead."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_FaceSculpting_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d0ab0e517194c2b3</T>
      <T n="text">0xBB343B14<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Rotate</font></b> your Sim to access even more Drag options! For example, nose length can only be edited from the side view."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\CAS\CAS_FaceSculpting_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d0ab0e517194c2b0</T>
      <T n="text">0xF4B10C91<!--String: "But wait, there’s more! While editing your Sim’s face, you can select the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Detail Edit Mode</font></b> button to get access to even more detailed click and drag options. For example, you can adjust the width and thickness of your Sim’s upper and lower lip, independently of one another!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
